Surfer

Target IP: 10.10.63.86
Challenge Description:

Reconnaissance


Doing a port scan shows there are two TCP ports open on the target machine.


I performed an aggressive port scan against the two open TCP ports and obtained the result above. The HTTP application on port 80 is interesting. The scan found the interesting robots.txt which contains the entry /backup/chat.txt.

Enumeration, Exploitation, and Flag

Port 80: HTTP

I started enumeration with the /backup/chat.txt. The chat log contains the information above. It seems like the internal server is hosting the flag. And the target machine is running export2pdf tool. Also, the admin is using the default credentials admin:admin according to the chat log above.


Browsing to this port displays the login webpage above.


I tried the default credentials admin:admin and got access! The webpage above is displayed to me after logging in successfully. On the right-hand side, it states there is an internal page hosted at /internal/admin.php. However, browsing to /internal/admin.php gives me the error message This page can only be accessed locally.. From previous enumeration, I know the target machine is using export2pdf. Maybe I can use this to access the internal page?


Scrolling to the bottom on the webpage, there is a button that can be pressed to use the export2pdf application.


Pressing the button from the previous image displays the webpage above. It displays more information about the web server.


Using Burpsuite, I intercepted the request after pressing the Export to PDF button. I notice there is a parameter called url that can be modified. This export2pdf uses this URL. I changed the url parameter to http%3A%2F%2F127.0.0.1%2Finternal%2Fadmin.php, as shown above.


The server sent a HTTP 200 response code. I right-clicked on the response, clicked the Show response in browser button, copied & pasted the response URL in my browser and obtained the flag above. GG. This was a fun SSRF challenge.
